content.description: Start on a rock with an X carved into it. Go up with good holds to an awesome pinch and make some scary moves at the top.
content.location: Located on the West face. Around the corner to the right from the rest of the problems.

content.description: Start in two pockets at about 5 feet. Set up and make a big move to a shitty 2 finger pocket, lock-off and move into the mono.  Set up again and go out right to a sloping dish/pocket and top out. Stout....
content.location: #2 on the route guide pictre. The line in the middle on the NW face.

content.description: Sit start down low in a crack and move up to the big hold. Throw a drop knee and go out left to a pinch in some pockets. Heel hook and hit the next crimp.
content.location: #3 on the route guide picture. The rightmost route on the NW face.

content.description: Start on two half pad crimps almost at 6 feet.  Set your feet up in little pockets and fire up to one of three pockets right next to each other. Hit it and drop in to one of the other pockets and then make a big move to a crimper pocket before topping out.
content.location: This route is #1 in the guide picture and the leftmost on the NW face.

content.description:
This problem has some intense pocket pulling and bad footholds with tricky-to- read beta. Good luck finding a solution to this problem!

If anyone knows of a name or previous ascent, please do not hesitate to let me know!
content.protection: 2 pads and a maybe a roll of tape if you have thin skin.
content.location:
Start on the jug of

Notorious

, and immediately traverse left through the pockets towards the left arete of the boulder.
